@*
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    _Imports.razor — Phase 7.1 (design decision 3): the project-wide Razor
    imports for every .razor page in BlazorNative.Components.

    The Components.Web line is LOAD-BEARING, twice over, and its absence is
    the spike's recorded footgun (7.0 conclusion §"The footgun"): bind and
    event tag helpers are namespace-scoped like components, so WITHOUT this
    @using in scope the compiler emits `@bind`/`@onclick` as LITERAL MARKUP —
    AddMarkupContent("<input @bind=\"_text\">") — with ZERO diagnostics and a
    green build. The binding is silently dead; on a native shell the markup
    renders as nothing at all (the renderer's Markup rule). Putting the line
    HERE makes that failure mode structurally impossible per page instead of
    a per-file discipline. It also scopes MouseEventArgs for @onclick and
    Components.Web's built-in BindAttributes, which declare exactly our wire
    (input → value + onchange — the pair BnInput hand-wires).
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*@
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Web
@using BlazorNative.Components
@using BlazorNative.Core
